{{notability|date=February 2013}} '''Danyahira Sirpa''' is an [[award]] given for the best people in the field of [[Nepal Bhasa]]. This [[award]] get its name from the names of Dana Ratna, Yagna Ratna & Hira Devi Dhakhwa. It is an [[award]] of fifty thousand rupees along with a citation on copper plaque is presented annually to a person or group that has made outstanding contributions or achievements in the field of [[Newari literature]] or [[Newa music|music]].<ref name=autogenerated1>[http://www.nepalbhashaacademy.org.np/awards.htm Nepal Bhasha Academy :: Our Projects, Awards<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20120906233746/http://www.nepalbhashaacademy.org.np/awards.htm |date=2012-09-06 }}</ref> The award was started from 2004.
